   348	
   349	### D.7 Implementer changes
   350	
   351	The implementer's existing flow per [chapter 03 §3.2](../../spec/v0/03-roles.md):
   352	
   353	```text
   354	1. Store.create_trial(status="starting")
   355	2. git worktree add <path> <parent>
   356	3. <user command writes commits>
   357	4. repo.create_ref("refs/heads/work/<…>", commit_sha)
   358	5. Store.submit(...)
   359	```
   360	
   361	becomes:
   362	
   363	```text
   364	1. Store.create_trial(status="starting")
   365	2. git worktree add <path> <parent>      # local
   366	3. <user command writes commits>
   367	4. repo.create_ref("refs/heads/work/<…>")  # local
   368	5. repo.push_ref("refs/heads/work/<…>")    # publish to Gitea
   369	6. Store.submit(...)
   370	```
   371	
   372	The submit's `commit_sha` is the local SHA that we just pushed.
   373	If push fails, we roll back the local ref (so the trial doesn't
   374	linger as a "starting" trial that references a non-published
   375	commit) and submit `status="error"`.
   376	
   377	### D.8 Evaluator changes
   378	
   379	The evaluator runs **before** integration, so the commit it
   380	must check out lives on the implementer's `work/*` branch
   381	(stored as `trial.branch` and `trial.commit_sha` per chapter
   382	3 §3.2 step 3) — NOT on `trial/*`, which is the post-integration
   383	namespace.
   384	
   385	After cutover, the evaluator's pre-worktree-add step is:
   386	
   387	```python
   388	repo.fetch_ref(trial.branch)        # work/<slug>-<trial_id>
   389	# fetch_ref returns the remote SHA; assert it equals
   390	# trial.commit_sha or surface eval_error
   391	repo.task_worktree_add(commit=trial.commit_sha)
   392	```
   393	
   394	The chapter-3 contract is unchanged; only the local fetch is
   395	added so the worker's clone sees the implementer's freshly-
   396	pushed commit. Evaluator never pushes.
   397	
   398	### D.8a Bare-clone topology for ALL worker hosts
   399	
   400	The current implementer/evaluator hosts use `git worktree add`
   401	against a bare repo (`TaskWorktree` in
   402	[`reference/services/_common/src/eden_service_common/worktrees.py`](../../reference/services/_common/src/eden_service_common/worktrees.py)
   403	takes a bare-repo path). Bare-clone topology is preserved
   404	post-cutover for ALL worker hosts:
   405	
   406	- orchestrator / integrator: bare clone
   407	- implementer host: bare clone
   408	- evaluator host: bare clone
   409	- web-ui (chunk-9c implementer module + chunk-9e admin
   410	  work-refs GC): bare clone
   411	
   412	`git worktree add` works fine against a bare repo; that's how
   413	chunk-10d already runs. The `clone_from` operation passes
   414	`--bare` unconditionally for worker hosts.
   415	
   416	The startup-refresh fetch becomes:
   417	
   418	```bash
   419	git fetch --prune origin '+refs/heads/*:refs/heads/*'
   420	```
   421	
   422	`--prune` removes local heads that no longer exist on remote
   423	(orphan-cleanup as a side effect of fetch). This works on bare
   424	repos because there's no checked-out branch to refuse-update.
