   487	### Unit (`reference/packages/eden-git/tests/test_remote_ops.py`)
   488	
   489	Run against a local file-URL git remote (`file:///path/to/bare`)
   490	— no Gitea daemon, no http. Sufficient because git's transport
   491	abstraction makes file:// share the same ref-update code path as
   492	http:// for our four new operations.
   493	
   494	- `GitRepo.clone_from(url=file://…, dest=…)` produces a working
   495	  clone at `dest`.
   496	- `GitRepo.push_ref(ref, expected_old_sha)` succeeds when the
   497	  remote ref matches `expected_old_sha`; raises `RefRefused`
   498	  when the remote has diverged.
   499	- `GitRepo.fetch_ref(ref)` updates the local ref to match
   500	  remote; returns the fetched SHA.
   501	- `GitRepo.delete_remote_ref(ref, expected_sha)` succeeds when
   502	  the remote matches; raises `RefRefused` on divergence; raises
   503	  `RefRefused` (not silent success) when the remote ref is
   504	  already gone (idempotency caveat: callers handle the
   505	  already-gone case explicitly because chapter-6 §3.4
   506	  rollback semantics distinguish "no-op" from "won the race").
   507	- Credential-helper roundtrip: drive a real `git http-backend`
   508	  via Python's `http.server` + the helper script generated by
   509	  setup-experiment's template. Assert that without the helper
   510	  the push fails 401, with the helper the push succeeds. This
   511	  proves the helper is wired correctly end-to-end at unit
   512	  speed; argv-only inspection would NOT.
   513	
