 succeeded in 0ms:
   676	  them. For orphan `trial/*` refs that ended up REMOTELY
   677	  published (the §D.6 step-4a-failed case), §D.7c's
   678	  store-authoritative reconciliation pass handles cleanup at
   679	  integrator startup.
   680	- **Credential exposure.** The credential-helper script lives
   681	  on the host filesystem with mode 0755 (executable; mounted
   682	  ro into the worker). Any process on the host with read
   683	  access can grab the password. This matches the existing
   684	  soft-isolation posture; documented in §7 of the
   685	  reference-binding chapter alongside the existing DooD
   686	  caveats. Hardened deployments substitute Docker secrets,
   687	  Vault, or sysbox-isolated workers; the wrap shape is
   688	  unchanged in those deployments.
   689	- **Push-rejected during integration.** If two integrators race
   690	  and one's push gets `RefRefused`, the loser runs §D.6 step
   691	  4b (local rollback). No `trial.integrated` was emitted yet
   692	  (only step 3 emits it), so the event log stays consistent.
   693	- **Store-write-after-push failure.** The §D.6 step-4a flow
   694	  ensures the remote ref is deleted before the local one if
   695	  the store write fails. If 4a itself fails, the §D.7c
   696	  reconciliation pass at the next integrator startup catches
   697	  the orphaned remote ref.
   698	- **Gitea downtime.** Workers exit on Gitea-unreachable;
   699	  compose restarts them. Brief Gitea downtime should not lose
   700	  data (workers just re-fetch when Gitea comes back); a
   701	  mid-task Gitea outage maps to the role-specific failure
   702	  contract per §D.7d above.
   703	- **Plain HTTP transport.** All git traffic is unencrypted on
   704	  the compose internal network. This is identical posture to
   705	  the existing reference's `EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN` plain-HTTP
   706	  traffic between workers and the task-store-server; the
   707	  trust boundary is the compose network, not the wire.
   708	  Hardened deployments terminate TLS at a sidecar or
   709	  Gitea-side reverse proxy.

